data.text:
August 10, 1979 was a Friday and it was the 222nd day of the year 1979 in the Gregorian calendar.

August 10, 1979 can also be written as 8/10/1979 in the US and as 10/8/1979 in UK and Europe.

The Zodiac and Astrological sign for August 10th is Leo.

Leo is the 5th sign in the Western Zodiac. People born between July 23rd and August 22nd belong to the Leo sign: discover Leo personality and who should a Leo marry.

Babies born in August are either Leo or Virgo. People born before August 22nd are Leo, while people born from August 23rd have the sign of Virgo.

Moon phase

The moon phase on August 10, 1979 was Waning gibbous.

The moon phase refers to the appearance of the Moon in the night sky on August 10, 1979 and is determined by the portion of the Moon's illuminated surface that is visible from Earth.

An observer located in New York City on August 10, 1979 at 10pm, would see the moon, being 83% full, rising at 09:47 pm and setting at 10:07 am.

The previous full moon was on Aug 08, 1979 while the next full moon would come on Sep 06, 1979.
